<div id="outline-container-org554eee1" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org554eee1">Correctness</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org554eee1">
<p>
We need to prove that an algorithm always returns the wanted output of all "legal" problems.
Algorithms must be specified to allow for a "provable" algorithm to exist, you find the quickest tour and not the best one.
</p>

<p>
The solution must be well defined, what would you mean by "best".
</p>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org72b407d" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org72b407d">Proofs</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org72b407d">
<p>
Proofs are to why something is correct, algorithms are ideas behind a problem.
you need to know why its correct if you dont you are probably wrong.
</p>
</div>
